<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF3C6A83FD0F94701D28BFF2" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF3C6A83FD0F94701D28BFF2" blockId="199.[753,1347,435,862]" lastBlockId="199.[131,1347,867,3190]" pageId="199" pageNumber="961">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FC7894701DD9B978" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[900,985,553,586]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FC1594701A7CB978" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1001,1148,553,586]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">montivagus</taxonomicName>
species group (9 species). 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FC55940C1A8EB940" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[937,1166,597,626]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annectans">Myotis annectans</taxonomicName>
was initially classified under genera 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FB9794211AF7B9AB" authorityName="Kaup" authorityYear="1829" box="[1131,1271,632,665]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pipistrellus</taxonomicName>
and Vesperugo and subgenus Megapipistrellus (now synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FBEC949E1A6AB9DA" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[1040,1130,711,744]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
). G. Topal in 1970 compared original type specimens with new specimens collected at the type locality and found that the holotype was an abnormal specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FE07953A1C4FB8B6" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[507,591,867,900]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
lacking P® and P, and clarified usage of species name, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FF7195D21F0EB89E" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[141,270,907,940]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annectans">annectans</taxonomicName>
. M. Ruedi and colleagues in 2013 and 2015 found that 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FBE795D21ACBB89E" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[1051,1227,907,940]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annectans">M. annectans</taxonomicName>
was one of four “floating” species in a monotypic lineage with unsettled phylogenetic position in this Eurasian assemblage. This lineage was positioned near a clade including 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FB1795831ED2BF10" authorityName="Maeda &amp; Matsumura" authorityYear="1998" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yanbarensis">yanbarensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FF1992581F58BF10" box="[229,344,1025,1058]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="secundus">secundus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FE9492581FE9BF10" authorityName="Yoshiyuki" authorityYear="1971" box="[360,489,1025,1058]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pruinosus">pruinosus</taxonomicName>
, and montivaguscomplex and a clade including 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FB6192581B3ABF10" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[1181,1338,1025,1058]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">cf. muricola</taxonomicName>
, cf. ateri, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FEC292681FC8BF78" authorityName="Kruskop &amp; Borisenko" authorityYear="2013" box="[318,456,1073,1098]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annatessae">annatessae</taxonomicName>
. Other recent studies have found various associations of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FB1492681EEBBF40" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="967" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annectans">M. annectans</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FEE092001C17BF40" authorityName="Hill &amp; Francis" authorityYear="1998" box="[284,535,1113,1138]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gomantongensis">M. gomantongensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FDD492001CD8BF40" authorityName="Yoshiyuki" authorityYear="1971" box="[552,728,1113,1138]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pruinosus">M. pruinosus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FD1692001DAFBF40" authorityName="Maeda &amp; Matsumura" authorityYear="1998" box="[746,943,1113,1138]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yanbarensis">M. yanbarensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FC3D92001A65BF40" box="[961,1125,1113,1138]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="secundus">M. secundus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FB8B92001B39BF40" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1143,1337,1113,1138]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">cf. montivagus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FF7792251F69BFAB" box="[139,361,1148,1177]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="indochinensis">M. indochinensis</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FE4092251C1CBFAB" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[444,540,1148,1177]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="959" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">M. ater</taxonomicName>
. More research is needed to determine relationships of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FF7792C61F3BBFF2" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[139,315,1183,1216]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="967" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annectans">M. annectans</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FE6292C61FF2BFF2" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[414,498,1183,1216]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
radiation. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF3C6A83FF76929E1D89BE04" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" type="distribution">
