</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF3C6A83FF7F9C221C80B00B" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" type="activity">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF3C6A83FF7F9C221C80B00B" blockId="199.[131,1347,867,3190]" pageId="199" pageNumber="961">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF3C6A83FF7F9C221F6EB1AE" bold="true" box="[131,366,2683,2716]" pageId="199" pageNumber="961">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The Hairy-faced 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FD949C221CC2B1AE" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[616,706,2683,2716]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
is nocturnal and seems to be an aerial hawker, with powerful flight similar to that of medium-sized serotines. In 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF3C6A83FBC69CFA1B33B1F6" box="[1082,1331,2723,2756]" country="Vietnam" name="Dak Lak" pageId="199" pageNumber="961">Dak Lak Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF3C6A83FF7F9C931EF5B1D9" box="[131,245,2762,2795]" name="Vietnam" pageId="199" pageNumber="961">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
,it was captured over a forest trail at ¢. 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3C6A83FCD79C931D9AB1D9" box="[811,922,2762,2795]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" unit="m" value="1100.0">1100 m</quantity>
. In 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF3C6A83FC2B9C931A69B1D9" box="[983,1129,2762,2795]" name="Cambodia" pageId="199" pageNumber="961">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
, it had steeply FM calls, without any CF component; calls (durations 2:1-2-8 milliseconds) started at c.80 kHz and swept down to 30 kHz.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF3C6A83FF789D191A30B053" box="[132,1072,2880,2913]" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF3C6A83FF789D191A30B053" blockId="199.[131,1347,867,3190]" box="[132,1072,2880,2913]" pageId="199" pageNumber="961">
