</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF3C6A83FF789D311A08B0E5" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF3C6A83FF789D311A08B0E5" blockId="199.[131,1347,867,3190]" pageId="199" pageNumber="961">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF3C6A83FF789D311FE0B0BB" bold="true" box="[132,480,2920,2953]" pageId="199" pageNumber="961">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Hairyfaced 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3C6A83FF279DD61F34B082" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[219,308,2959,2992]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="961" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
is widespread, presumably has a large population, and is unlikely to be declining fast enough to qualify for a more threatened category.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
